AKURE – Member House of Representatives representing Ondo East and West Federal Constituency, Abiola Makinde; with his wife; Dr. Rhoda Oluwatoberu Makinde, the CEO/Executive Director of Dr. Rhoda Makinde Initiative (DROMI), has distributed different gifts to the orphans across the state. The couple visited orphanage homes, churches, mosques, schools and other communities across the state Ondo distributing different food items, bicycles, toiletries, fabrics, cash among others to the underprivileged. Tagging the programme: “Let the Orphans Be Glad,” the lawmaker and his wife stated that it was a way of showing love for the fatherless. Ondo Boosts Security With CIG Pickups, Trucks, Others Bye-election: APC, PDP Adopt Indirect Primary Election In Ondo Converged at Oba Adesanoye Civic Centre, Ondo City, orphans and other beneficiaries were presented gifts and treated to some entertainment. Speaking on the programme, the federal legislator said: “This project is a joint initiative of both myself and my wife, Dr. Rhoda Makinde, the founder of DROMI. It is a genuine drive to reach out to the orphans in our community and to also give back to the community in our own little capacity.” His wife, Dr. Rhoda Makinde explained that “This is part of those things we do to give back to the community. Orphans are humans too, they should be fully taken care of. Losing their parents is not their fault.” As part of the entertainment session of the programme, the orphans were engaged in dancing competitions, raffle draws and other games attracting prizes including bicycles, food items and cash.